  target properties when creating the binding; the direction of
  the synchronization is always from the source to the target.</para>
</entry>
<entry role="enum_member_annotations"></entry>
</row>
<row role="constant"><entry role="enum_member_name"><para id="G-BINDING-INVERT-BOOLEAN:CAPS">G_BINDING_INVERT_BOOLEAN</para></entry>
<entry role="enum_member_description"><para>If the two properties being bound are
  booleans, setting one to <link linkend="TRUE:CAPS"><literal>TRUE</literal></link> will result in the other being
  set to <link linkend="FALSE:CAPS"><literal>FALSE</literal></link> and vice versa. This flag will only work for
  boolean properties, and cannot be used when passing custom
  transformation functions to <link linkend="g-object-bind-property-full"><function>g_object_bind_property_full()</function></link>.</para>
</entry>
<entry role="enum_member_annotations"></entry>
</row>
